{"word":"ἔλυτρον","slug":"ἔλυτρον","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔλυτρον</b></el> <el>(ἔλῠτρον, ου, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἐλύω'><el>ἐλύω</el></a> II\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>the case</i> of a spear, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the body</i> as <i>the case</i> of <i>the soul</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b> <a href='S:apud (quoted in)'>ap.</a> <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a place for holding water, a reservoir</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}